{
  "texts": [
    "Heatmaps can be viewed interactively and exported as both PNG images and Numpy arrays.",
    "Heatmap color and display options are customized in another tab of the interface (not shown)used, using default hyperparameters from the original implementation [58].",
    "Training was stopped after 15 million images due to divergence with further training.",
    "Training took 38 h on four A100 GPUs.",
    "Visualizations generated with this method highlighted differences in keratinization and nuclear pleomorphism, which is increased in the synthetic HPV-negative images, and inflammatory infiltrate, increased in synthetic HPVpositive images (Fig. 15B)."
  ]
}